An Armoured Fighting Vehicle (AFV) is a military vehicle designed to be used in combat. It is heavily armored to protect the soldiers inside and often has weapons mounted on it. AFVs come in many different shapes and sizes, from small tanks to massive troop carriers. They are used by armies all around the world for a variety of purposes, including transporting troops, providing fire support, and reconnaissance. Some of the most famous AFVs include the American M1 Abrams tank, the Russian T-90 tank, and the British Warrior Infantry Fighting Vehicle. These vehicles are carefully designed to be both tough and versatile, making them essential tools for modern militaries.
